Police were called to Wharncliffe Road, to the east of Liverpool city centre on Tuesday afternoon after receiving reports of a man carrying a gun. A number of police officers who attended the scene were carrying weapons. Photographs show armed officers near the property.  A nearby house also was seen to have a broken door in the Liverpool district of Old Swan. Merseyside Police rushed to the scene at 12.30pm, responding to a call from a member of the public. No gunman or firearm has yet been located. Merseyside Police has confirmed an operation is underway. READ MORE: £33m-winning family face almost 50 objections for Hollywood mansion  The Liverpool Echo reported seeing six police vehicles on the street as officers scoured the area. Anyone with information relating to the incident can contact @MerPolCC on Twitter or ‘Merseyside Police Contact Centre’ on Facebook. Alternatively, you can call 101 with reference 0350 of 5 April 2022. You can also call Crimestoppers, anonymously on 0800 555 111, or their online form. DON'T MISS: Royal Family LIVE: Harry and Meghan guests 'went off' at Sussex's [LIVE]Covid hotspots mapped: Which UK areas have the most cases? [MAP]POLL: Do you think Boris Johnson delivered a Brexit 'in name only'? [POLL]